claim.claim-text:
1. A method for characterizing free-space radiation, said method comprising: 
providing one of an electro-optic crystal or a magneto-optic crystal; 
positioning the crystal so that the free-space radiation passes therethrough; 
generating a chirped optical probe signal and co-propagating the chirped optical probe signal through the crystal with the free-space radiation such that a temporal waveform of the free-space radiation is encoded onto a wavelength spectrum of the chirped optical probe signal; and 
decoding a characteristic of said free-space radiation using said chirped optical probe signal with said temporal waveform of the free-space radiation encoded on its wavelength spectrum.
